SIMPLE: rat-tail
RECORDS: 2

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Rat-tail
<hw>Rat"-tail`</hw> <pr>(r⟦acr⟧t"t⟦amac⟧l`)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos>
<def>Like a rat's tail in form; <as>as, a <ex>rat-tail</ex> file, which
is round, slender, and tapering</as>. See <xex>Illust.</xex> of
<er>File</er>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Rat-tail</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Rat-tail
<hw>Rat"-tail`</hw>, <pos>n.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <fld>(Far.)</fld>
<pluf>pl.</pluf> <def>An excrescence growing from the pastern to the
middle of the shank of a horse.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <fld>(Zool.)</fld> <sd>(a)</sd> <def>The California
chimaera. See <er>Chimaera</er>.</def> <sd>(b)</sd> <def>Any fish of the
genus <gen>Macrurus</gen>. See <er>Grenadier</er>, 2.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Rat-tailed</ent>⟦br⟧
